00:54:08,639 --> 00:54:10,700
This is what it would look like if it was a pure circle.

1263
00:54:11,440 --> 00:54:13,281
And this is kind of what it ended up like.

1264
00:54:14,581 --> 00:54:16,762
So you have to start wondering, once we've

1265
00:54:16,782 --> 00:54:22,365
got this structural center and we have these pathways which

1266
00:54:22,425 --> 00:54:25,267
are retained very clearly, how else can we

1267
00:54:25,307 --> 00:54:27,788
accentuate the hub-like nature while also delivering

1268
00:54:27,828 --> 00:54:28,429
on the organics?

1269
00:54:28,909 --> 00:54:31,130
And the answer was that all around the Lake of Nine,

1270
00:54:31,250 --> 00:54:32,571
there's these additional towers.

1271
00:54:32,991 --> 00:54:35,593
And even though they may not necessarily

1272
00:54:35,653 --> 00:54:38,234
create a pure circle, per se, in terms of a barrier,

1273
00:54:38,514 --> 00:54:40,836
they do help to create an additional anchor that

1274
00:54:40,876 --> 00:54:41,996
helps us emphasize the hub.

1275
00:54:42,617 --> 00:54:44,378
So even though the level itself became more organic,

1276
00:54:44,398 --> 00:54:46,439
there's still enough hub-like elements

1277
00:54:46,479 --> 00:54:48,420
that we can retain the core design intent

1278
00:54:48,740 --> 00:54:51,441
while also supporting the needs of the environment art team.

1279
00:54:54,283 --> 00:54:54,423
So.

1280
00:54:55,563 --> 00:54:57,544
I mentioned at the top of the presentation

1281
00:54:57,584 --> 00:55:00,026
that this project actually did have a lot of risks, right?

1282
00:55:00,747 --> 00:55:02,408
And even though from a technical standpoint,

1283
00:55:02,468 --> 00:55:03,809
areas like the Lake of Nine, which

1284
00:55:03,849 --> 00:55:07,111
was created and led by Luis Sanchez and John Palamarchuk,

1285
00:55:07,551 --> 00:55:09,092
they worked on it for a long time.

1286
00:55:09,132 --> 00:55:13,075
And it was a huge technical task to get it up and running.

1287
00:55:13,856 --> 00:55:15,757
But the nice thing about some of these design rules

1288
00:55:15,817 --> 00:55:18,339
is that they're pretty easy for us to understand and get

